name: Spinosella Flameus
description:
--Fig.18--
Spinosella Flameus is a creature from Saffar, an exoplanet located 43 light years from Earth, orbiting the star Titawin.
The first years of Spinosella's life are spent in huge colonies formed by millions of cocoons, where they feed on minerals from the land to build their body. After they're full developed, they fly around the globe and may resist great sandstorms. As they are nocturnal animals, they use their bright tail tip to see in the dark and call for mates, not worrying with predators as they're almost pure rock.
